The paper discusses an automated machine learning approach for multi-label classification, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of MEKA, a multi-label extension of the Java library WEKA, which suggests a focus on software engineering and programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-label classifiers for image classification, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed approach compared to a set of baselines, which suggests a possible connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and evaluation methodologies.
